This paper is primarily focused on the stability of graph neural networks (GNNs), which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the discriminative power of GNNs, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve movie recommendation systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of linear graph filters, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS).
